## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="a0ddf-106">Você deve chamar o <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectoryEntry.CommitChanges%2A> método na nova entrada para tornar a criação permanente.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a0ddf-106">You must call the <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectoryEntry.CommitChanges%2A> method on the new entry to make the creation permanent.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="a0ddf-107">Quando você chama esse método, você pode definir valores de propriedade obrigatória na nova entrada.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a0ddf-107">When you call this method, you can then set mandatory property values on the new entry.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="a0ddf-108">Os provedores têm requisitos diferentes para as propriedades que precisam ser definidas antes de uma chamada para o <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectoryEntry.CommitChanges%2A> método é feito.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a0ddf-108">The providers each have different requirements for properties that need to be set before a call to the <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectoryEntry.CommitChanges%2A> method is made.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="a0ddf-109">Se esses requisitos não forem atendidos, o provedor pode gerar uma exceção.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a0ddf-109">If those requirements are not met, the provider might throw an exception.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="a0ddf-110">Verifique com seu provedor para determinar quais propriedades devem ser definidas antes de confirmar as alterações.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a0ddf-110">Check with your provider to determine which properties must be set before committing changes.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="a0ddf-111">O exemplo de Visual Basic .NET a seguir cria um novo <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectoryEntry> com um caminho especificado do objeto, em seguida, cria uma nova entrada no contêiner e salva-o.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a0ddf-111">The following Visual Basic .NET example creates a new <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectoryEntry> object with a specified path, then creates a new entry in the container and saves it.</span></span>  
  
```vb  
Dim strPath As String = "IIS://localhost/W3SVC/1/Root"  
' Create a new 'DirectoryEntry' object with the given path.  
Dim myDE As New DirectoryEntry(strPath)  
Dim myEntries As DirectoryEntries = myDE.Children  
' Create a new entry 'Sample' in the container.  
Dim myDirectoryEntry As DirectoryEntry = myEntries.Add("CN=Sample", myDE.SchemaClassName)  
' Save changes of entry in the 'Active Directory Domain Services'.  
myDirectoryEntry.CommitChanges()  
Console.WriteLine(myDirectoryEntry.Name + " entry is created in container.")  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="a0ddf-112">O exemplo c# a seguir cria um novo <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectoryEntry> com um caminho especificado do objeto, em seguida, cria uma nova entrada no contêiner e salva-o.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a0ddf-112">The following C# example creates a new <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectoryEntry> object with a specified path, then creates a new entry in the container and saves it.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
